## React Components

### Component Structure

- **Client Components**: Use `"use client"` directive at the top
- **Component Types**: Use `React.FC<PropsType>` for functional components
- **Props**: Use `type` definitions (not `interface`) for component props
  ```typescript
  type LogoLinkProps = {
    className?: string;
    src: string;
    alt: string;
  };
  ```
- **Function Style**: Use arrow functions for components
- **Props Destructuring**: In function parameters
- **Export**: Default export at the bottom

### Prop Ordering

When passing props to components or HTML elements, follow this order:

1. **`children`** (if passed as a prop) - must come first
2. **`id`** (if present) - must come second
3. **`className`** (if present) - must come third
4. **`style`** (if present) - must come fourth
5. **`key`** (if present) - must come fifth
6. **`src`** (if present) - must come sixth
7. **`alt`** (if present) - must come seventh
8. **`href`** (if present) - must come eighth
9. **`fill`** (if present) - must come ninth
10. **`sizes`** (if present) - must come tenth
11. **`width`** (if present) - must come eleventh
12. **`height`** (if present) - must come twelfth
13. **All other props** - in alphabetical order
14. **Event handlers** - must come last: `onClick`, `onMouseEnter`, `onMouseLeave` (in that order if multiple are present)

**Note**: In JSX, `children` is typically the content between opening and closing tags, not a prop. However, if `children` is explicitly passed as a prop (e.g., `children={content}`), it should come first.

**Examples:**
```typescript
// ✅ Correct - className before other props
<Button className="primary" disabled={false} onClick={handleClick}>
  Click me
</Button>

// ✅ Correct - id, className, key, then other props
{items.map((item) => (
  <Card
    id={`card-${item.id}`}
    className="card"
    key={item.id}
    title={item.title}
  >
    {item.content}
  </Card>
))}

// ✅ Correct - children prop first (when passed explicitly), then id, className
<Wrapper children={content} id="main" className="wrapper">
  {fallbackContent}
</Wrapper>

// ✅ Correct - id, className, then other props
<div id="main" className="container" onClick={handleClick}>
  {children}
</div>

// ✅ Correct - className, style, then other props
<div className="container" style={{ margin: 10 }} onClick={handleClick}>
  {children}
</div>

// ✅ Correct - Image props in correct order
<Image
  className="object-contain"
  src="/logo.png"
  alt="Logo"
  fill={true}
  sizes="100vw"
/>

// ✅ Correct - Image with width and height
<Image
  className="object-contain"
  src="/logo.png"
  alt="Logo"
  width={512}
  height={512}
  priority={true}
/>

// ✅ Correct - href after alt, event handlers at the end
<Link
  className="link"
  href="/page"
  target="_blank"
  onClick={handleClick}
>
  Click me
</Link>

// ✅ Correct - event handlers at the end
<Button
  className="primary"
  disabled={false}
  onClick={handleClick}
  onMouseEnter={handleMouseEnter}
  onMouseLeave={handleMouseLeave}
>
  Click me
</Button>

// ❌ Incorrect - other props before className
<Button onClick={handleClick} className="primary" disabled={false}>
  Click me
</Button>

// ❌ Incorrect - key before className
{items.map((item) => (
  <Card key={item.id} title={item.title} className="card">
    {item.content}
  </Card>
))}

// ❌ Incorrect - className before id
<div className="container" id="main" onClick={handleClick}>
  {children}
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect - style before className
<div style={{ margin: 10 }} className="container" onClick={handleClick}>
  {children}
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect - Image props out of order
<Image
  src="/logo.png"
  className="object-contain"
  alt="Logo"
  fill={true}
/>

// ❌ Incorrect - alt before src
<Image
  className="object-contain"
  alt="Logo"
  src="/logo.png"
  fill={true}
/>

// ❌ Incorrect - href before alt
<Link
  className="link"
  href="/page"
  alt="Link"
  onClick={handleClick}
>
  Click me
</Link>

// ❌ Incorrect - event handlers not at the end
<Button
  className="primary"
  onClick={handleClick}
  disabled={false}
>
  Click me
</Button>
```

