## Comments

### General Rules

- **Purpose**: Explain "why", not "what" - code should be sufficiently commented to explain structure and purpose
- **Syntax**: Use JSX comment syntax: `{/* Comment text */}`
- **Format**: Sentence case - capitalize first word and proper nouns. Use consistent writing style throughout the codebase
- **Length**: Maximum 80 characters (including spaces before comment, full line)
- **No periods**: Do not end comments with periods
- **Placement**: On their own line, immediately before the element they describe
- **Empty line above**: Always add an empty line above each comment, except when the comment is the first line within a code block or HTML element
- **Never use inline comments**: Comments must always be on their own line, never on the same line as code
- **No consecutive comments**: Never put 2 or more consecutive comments (applies to both JSX comments `{/* */}` and single-line comments `//`) - there must be code between comments
- **Sufficient commenting**: All major sections, elements, and logical groups should have comments explaining their purpose

### Comment Examples

```typescript
// ✅ Correct - with empty line above
return (
  <div>
    {/* Container */}
    <div>...</div>

    {/* Logo */}
    <LogoLink />

    {/* Navigation links */}
    <nav>...</nav>
  </div>
);

// ✅ Correct - first line in block (no empty line above)
return (
  <div>
    {/* Container */}
    <div>...</div>
  </div>
);

// ✅ Correct - first line in element (no empty line above)
<div>
  {/* Content */}
  <span>...</span>
</div>

// ❌ Incorrect
{/* container */}  // lowercase
{/* Container. */}  // has period
{/* This is a very long comment that exceeds 80 characters */}  // too long
const x = 5; {/* Inline comment */}  // inline comment not allowed
<div>{/* Inline comment */}</div>  // inline comment not allowed
{/* First comment */}
{/* Second comment */}
<div>...</div>  // consecutive JSX comments not allowed
// First comment
// Second comment
const x = 5;  // consecutive single-line comments not allowed
<div>
  {/* Missing empty line above */}
  <span>...</span>
</div>
```

### Block Component Comments

**Note**: These rules apply specifically to **block components** in `src/blocks`. Components in `src/components` have fewer comment requirements.

**Common Patterns:**
- Container: `{/* Container */}`
- Elements: `{/* Logo */}`, `{/* Text */}`, `{/* Image */}`, `{/* Heading */}`
- Groups: `{/* Links */}`, `{/* Buttons */}`, `{/* Navigation links */}`
- Sections: `{/* Contact information */}`, `{/* Legal links */}`, `{/* Copyright */}`
- Context: `{/* Navigation bar (desktop) */}`, `{/* Background image for mobile screens */}`
- Composite: `{/* Text and dropdown arrow */}`, `{/* Logo and contact container */}`
- Nested: `{/* Sublinks */}`, `{/* Dropdown list */}`
- Custom: `{/* USPs container */}` (capitalize proper nouns/acronyms)

**Guidelines:**
- Mark major sections and elements in the component tree
- Be descriptive but concise
- Include device/context in parentheses when relevant: `(desktop)`, `(mobile)`
- Comment every major section/element
- Use consistent naming patterns

