## Styling

### Colors

- **Custom colors must be defined in `src/app/styles.css`**: Custom colors are defined as CSS custom properties in the `@theme` section
- **Naming Convention**: Custom colors are defined with `--color-*` prefix (e.g., `--color-primary-purple`, `--color-dark`)
- **Usage in Tailwind**: Use the color name without the `--color-` prefix in Tailwind classes
  - CSS: `--color-primary-purple: #8c52fe;`
  - Tailwind: `bg-primary-purple`, `text-primary-purple`, `border-primary-purple`
- **Basic colors exception**: The colors `black`, `white`, and `gray` (with variants like `gray-100`, `gray-500`, etc.) are allowed and do not need to be defined in `styles.css`
- **Never use other Tailwind default colors**: Do not use Tailwind's default color palette for other colors (e.g., `bg-blue-500`, `text-red-600`, `border-slate-300`, `bg-indigo-100`, etc.)
- **Never use hardcoded color values**: Do not use hex codes, rgb(), or other color values directly in className (except for basic black, white, and gray)
- **Opacity**: Use Tailwind opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-primary-purple/20`, `text-dark/80`)

**Examples:**
```typescript
// ❌ Don't use Tailwind default colors
className="bg-blue-500"
className="text-red-600"
className="border-gray-300"
className="bg-slate-100"
className="text-indigo-700"

// ❌ Don't use hardcoded colors
className="bg-[#8c52fe]"
className="text-[#222222]"
className="border-[rgb(140,82,254)]"

// ✅ Use colors from styles.css
className="bg-primary-purple"
className="text-dark"
className="border-primary-purple/20"
className="text-dark/80"
```

**Defining New Colors:**
1. Add the color to `src/app/styles.css` in the `@theme` section: `--color-{name}: {value};`
2. Use the color in Tailwind classes: `bg-{name}`, `text-{name}`, `border-{name}`, etc.

### Typography

- **Always use hardcoded pixel values**: `text-[15px]`, `text-[14px]`, `text-[12px]`
- **Never use Tailwind default text size classes**: Do not use `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`, `text-2xl`, etc.

**Examples:**
```typescript
// ❌ Don't use
className="text-sm"
className="text-lg"
className="text-base"

// ✅ Use
className="text-[15px]"
className="text-[14px]"
className="text-[12px]"
```

### Gradients

- **Always use `bg-linear-to-*` instead of `bg-gradient-to-*`**: Use `bg-linear-to-br`, `bg-linear-to-r`, `bg-linear-to-t`, etc.
- **Never use `bg-gradient-to-*`**: Do not use Tailwind's default `bg-gradient-to-*` classes

**Examples:**
```typescript
// ❌ Don't use
className="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-200 to-gray-300"
className="bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-purple to-primary-lightpurple"

// ✅ Use
className="bg-linear-to-br from-gray-200 to-gray-300"
className="bg-linear-to-r from-primary-purple to-primary-lightpurple"
```

### Aspect Ratios

- **Use simplified syntax when available**: Use `aspect-4/3` instead of `aspect-[4/3]` when Tailwind supports the fractional value directly
- **Use arbitrary values for uncommon ratios**: Use `aspect-[21/9]` for ratios that aren't commonly supported

**Examples:**
```typescript
// ❌ Don't use (when simpler syntax is available)
className="aspect-[4/3]"

// ✅ Use (simpler syntax)
className="aspect-4/3"

// ✅ Use (uncommon ratio requires arbitrary value)
className="aspect-[21/9]"
```

### Flexbox Utilities

- **Use simplified syntax**: Use `shrink-0` instead of `flex-shrink-0`
- **Use `grow-*` and `shrink-*`**: Prefer the simplified flexbox utility classes

**Examples:**
```typescript
// ❌ Don't use
className="flex-shrink-0"
className="flex-grow-1"

// ✅ Use
className="shrink-0"
className="grow-1"
```

### className Formatting

#### twMerge Usage

**Use `twMerge` (from `tailwind-merge`) when:**
- The line of code would exceed 80 characters, OR
- There is a variable in the list of classes (like a `className` prop)

**Use simple string className when:**
- It fits within 80 characters AND
- Has no variables

**Never use template literal notation** with backticks for className

**Import:** `import { twMerge } from "tailwind-merge"`

**Examples:**
```typescript
// ❌ Don't use template literals
className={`
  flex items-center gap-4
  ${isActive ? "bg-blue" : "bg-gray"}
  ${className}
`}

// ✅ Simple string (fits in 80 chars, no variables)
className="flex items-center gap-4 bg-blue"

// ✅ twMerge (has variable)
className={twMerge("flex items-center gap-4", className)}

// ✅ twMerge (exceeds 80 chars)
className={twMerge(
  "flex items-center gap-4",
  isActive ? "bg-blue" : "bg-gray",
  className
)}
```

#### className Ordering

When using multiple lines, order classes in this sequence:

1. **Z-Index**: `z-*` (must come before positioning classes)
2. **Layout/Positioning**: `relative`, `absolute`, `fixed`
3. **Display/Visibility**: `flex`, `grid`, `block`, `hidden`
4. **Positioning**: `inset-*`, `top-*`, `bottom-*`, `left-*`, `right-*`, `translate-*` (z-index must come before these)
5. **Flexbox/Grid Properties**: `flex-col`, `flex-row`, `items-*`, `justify-*`, `gap-*`
6. **Sizing**: `w-*`, `min-w-*`, `max-w-*`, `h-*`, `min-h-*`, `max-h-*`
7. **Spacing**: `p-*`, `px-*`, `py-*`, `pt-*`, `pb-*`, `pl-*`, `pr-*`, `m-*`, `ml-*`, `mr-*`, `mt-*`, `mb-*`
8. **Typography**: `text-*`, `font-*`
   - Text sizes must use hardcoded pixel values (e.g., `text-[15px]`)
   - Never use Tailwind default text size classes
9. **Colors**: `bg-*`, `text-*`
10. **Borders**: `border-*`, `rounded-*`
11. **Effects**: `shadow-*`, `opacity-*`, `transition-*`, `duration-*`
12. **Responsive Breakpoints**: Prioritize `xs:*`, `de:*`, `me:*`
    - Other breakpoints (`sm:*`, `md:*`, `lg:*`, `xl:*`) available when needed
    - Prefer `xs:`, `de:`, and `me:` as primary breakpoints
13. **Custom Classes**: Project-specific classes (e.g., `container-medium`, `text-mediumsmall`)

#### Multi-line className

**Single line**: Use when classes fit comfortably on one line (typically 3-5 classes)
```typescript
className="flex items-center gap-4"
```

**Multi-line**: Use when:
- Responsive breakpoints on separate lines
- Conditional classes that need clarity
- Line would exceed 80 characters

**Formatting with twMerge:**
- **Group related classes together**: Don't split every single class onto its own line. Group classes from the same category (e.g., all spacing classes, all sizing classes) on the same line if they fit within 80 characters.
- **Each breakpoint on its own line**: Every responsive breakpoint (`xs:`, `de:`, `me:`, `md:`, `lg:`, etc.) must be on a separate line, even if it's just one class.
- **Base classes first**: Put all base (non-responsive) classes on the first line(s), then breakpoints.
- **Conditional classes clearly separated**: Put conditional classes on separate lines for clarity.

**Example:**
```typescript
// ✅ Good: Groups related classes together, breakpoints on separate lines
className={twMerge(
  "relative flex flex-col gap-8 w-5/6 max-w-120 mx-auto",
  "de:flex-row de:max-w-300",
  imageLeft && "de:flex-row-reverse",
  className
)}

// ✅ Good: Multiple base classes grouped, each breakpoint on its own line
className={twMerge(
  "flex items-center gap-4 p-6 rounded-xl bg-white",
  "xs:gap-6",
  "de:p-8 de:rounded-2xl",
  "me:gap-8",
  className
)}

// ❌ Bad: Too many lines, classes split unnecessarily
className={twMerge(
  "flex",
  "items-center",
  "gap-4",
  "p-6",
  "rounded-xl",
  "bg-white",
  "xs:gap-6",
  "de:p-8",
  "de:rounded-2xl",
)}

// ❌ Bad: Breakpoints not on separate lines
className={twMerge(
  "flex items-center gap-4 p-6 rounded-xl bg-white xs:gap-6 de:p-8",
)}
```

#### Responsive Breakpoints

- **Mobile-first approach**: Base classes first, then breakpoints
- **Breakpoint order**: `xs:*`, `sm:*`, `md:*`, `de:*`, `lg:*`, `me:*`, `xl:*`
- **Each breakpoint on its own line**: Every breakpoint must be on a separate line, even if it contains only one class
- **Group breakpoint classes**: When multiple classes share the same breakpoint, group them on the same line

**Example:**
```typescript
className={twMerge(
  "flex flex-col gap-18",
  "xs:flex-row xs:gap-20",
  "sm:gap-22",
  "md:flex-row",
  "de:flex-row de:justify-between",
  "lg:gap-24",
  "me:gap-16",
  "xl:gap-28",
  className
)}
```

