## TypeScript Best Practices

- **Never use `any` type**: The `any` type is strictly forbidden. Always use proper types, `unknown`, or generics instead
  - Use `unknown` when the type is truly unknown and needs runtime type checking
  - Use proper types when the structure is known
  - Use generics for reusable code with type parameters
  - ESLint rule `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any` is set to warn to catch this
- **Type Definitions**: Prefer `type` over `interface` for component props
- **Type Exports**: Export types using `export type` syntax
- **Generic Types**: Use generics when appropriate for reusable code
- **Type Guards**: Use type guards for runtime type checking when using `unknown`

