### Whitespace Rules

Use blank lines to separate logical sections of code:

1. **After "use client" directive**: Always add a blank line
   ```typescript
   "use client";
   
   import { ... }
   ```

2. **After imports**: Blank line before type definitions or component declarations
   ```typescript
   import { ... }
   
   type ComponentProps = { ... }
   ```

3. **After type definitions**: Blank line before const/component declarations
   ```typescript
   type ComponentProps = { ... }
   
   const Component: React.FC<ComponentProps> = () => { ... }
   ```

4. **After const declarations inside functions**: 
   - If multiple consts are related, keep them together
   - Add a blank line after the last const before the next logical section (return, useEffect, other functions, etc.)
   ```typescript
   const Component: React.FC = () => {
     const value1 = ...;
     const value2 = ...;
     const value3 = ...;
     
     useEffect(() => { ... }, []);
     
     return (...);
   };
   ```

5. **Between hooks and return**: Blank line between React hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.) and return statement
   ```typescript
   const [state, setState] = useState(...);
   useEffect(() => { ... }, []);
   
   return (...);
   ```

6. **Between function definitions**: Blank line between different function definitions within a component
   ```typescript
   const handleClick = () => { ... };
   
   const handleSubmit = () => { ... };
   
   return (...);
   ```

7. **Above return statements**: Always add a blank line above return statements, except when:
   - It is the first line within a code block (function body, if statement, etc.)
   - A comment is directly above it
   ```typescript
   // ✅ Correct - blank line above return
   const value = calculate();
   
   return value;
   
   // ✅ Correct - first line in function (no blank line needed)
   const Component: React.FC = () => {
     return <div>...</div>;
   };
   
   // ✅ Correct - comment above (no blank line needed)
   const value = calculate();
   // Return the calculated value
   return value;
   
   // ✅ Correct - first line in if block (no blank line needed)
   if (condition) {
     return <div>...</div>;
   }
   
   // ❌ Incorrect - missing blank line above return
   const value = calculate();
   return value;
   ```

8. **Between logical sections in JSX**: Blank lines between major JSX sections (separated by comments)
   ```typescript
   return (
     <div>
       {/* Section 1 */}
       <div>...</div>
       
       {/* Section 2 */}
       <div>...</div>
     </div>
   );
   ```

9. **Before export default**: Always add a blank line before export statement
   ```typescript
   };
   
   export default Component;
   ```
